Fine!

17:16.720 --> 17:18.994
Man, you owe me an apple.

17:19.640 --> 17:22.551
Would you keep it down?
l'm on the phone!

17:23.119 --> 17:25.349
Hey, Oliver, where are you?

17:26.720 --> 17:30.269
Great. Just meet us down at the studio.

17:30.320 --> 17:32.072
Okay, Oliver has to go down
to the police station

17:32.120 --> 17:34.111
and get the key from his mom,
and l've gotta get ready.

17:34.160 --> 17:37.197
Not until you buy me another apple.

17:37.240 --> 17:39.595
Forget about the apple.
Help me get ready

17:39.640 --> 17:42.154
and you can keep any three
Hannah outfits you want, okay?

17:42.200 --> 17:43.269
-What about shoes?
-One pair.

17:43.320 --> 17:45.311
-Two.
-Nothing ltalian.

17:46.600 --> 17:47.794
Fine.

17:52.200 --> 17:55.112
Okay.
This may be harder than we thought.

17:56.080 --> 17:58.355
-Yeah. Let's go change.
-Okay.

18:00.960 --> 18:04.032
Okay, this is definitely
not an improvement.

18:04.080 --> 18:05.877
Your feet stink!

18:05.920 --> 18:08.388
Yeah? How do you like them now?

18:11.840 --> 18:16.834
lt's a little tight, but l think it may work.
Let's go take a look in the mirror.

18:19.520 --> 18:20.873
Goodness.

18:21.440 --> 18:22.714
Lovely.

18:27.600 --> 18:31.388
Look at that. l knew you two
couldn't stay mad at each other.

18:31.440 --> 18:33.749
Yeah. We're closer than ever.

18:34.920 --> 18:37.036
You wanna tell me how this happened?

18:37.080 --> 18:38.433
Well, Oliver thought that if he put us...

18:38.480 --> 18:41.995
Sweet niblets,
l wish that boy would stop doing that.

18:42.040 --> 18:44.474
Well, none of this would've happened
if you would've just picked me.

18:44.520 --> 18:46.875
Yeah, l am not the one
who gave a limo ride to a plant.

18:46.920 --> 18:48.831
At least
if Fern was playing flag football,

18:48.880 --> 18:49.949
she would've just picked me.

18:50.000 --> 18:53.151
-lt's a ficus!
-Named Fern!

18:53.840 --> 18:57.469
You could not pay me enough money
to be a teenage girl.

18:57.520 --> 18:58.839
-l got the key, l got the key!
-Thank you.

18:58.880 --> 19:00.791
You're live in one minute,
Miss Montana.

19:00.840 --> 19:03.308
Get 'er done, son.
Carrie Underwood is on stage

19:03.360 --> 19:05.510
announcing that Hannah's
won the award right now.

19:05.560 --> 19:07.357
l haven't even thought
about what l'm going to say yet.

19:07.400 --> 19:08.799
Well, lucky for you, l did.

19:08.840 --> 19:10.751
All you gotta to do
is read the TelePrompTer.

19:10.800 --> 19:13.473
Your daddy's thought of everything.

19:14.440 --> 19:16.670
Except the key breaking.

19:17.280 --> 19:19.840
-Uh-oh.
-l hate when he says uh-oh.

19:19.880 --> 19:22.599
Yeah, it's almost as bad
as when he thinks.

19:22.640 --> 19:24.551
-Live in 30 seconds!
-Oh, boy.

19:24.600 --> 19:26.397
Gee, l wonder
what's gonna happen now.

19:26.440 --> 19:28.556
Gee, l wonder
what's gonna happen now.

19:28.600 --> 19:29.669
l have an idea!

19:29.720 --> 19:31.278
-No!
-No!

19:31.320 --> 19:34.357
Normally, l'd agree,
but this is a good one.

19:37.520 --> 19:41.718
<i>Accepting her award, live from</i>
<i>Los Angeles, Hannah Montana.</i>

19:42.360 --> 19:45.591
Thank you so much
for this incredible honour.

19:45.640 --> 19:47.198
And it means even more knowing

19:47.240 --> 19:49.470
that it's coming from
the good folks in Nashville,

19:49.520 --> 19:52.671
the place that l'm proud
to call my hometown.

19:53.520 --> 19:55.476
Hooray, Nashville!

19:56.600 --> 20:01.355
l only wish that l could be there
in person to tell you how l truly feel.

20:04.120 --> 20:08.238
This is my special wave to Grandma.
Hi, Grandma!

20:09.120 --> 20:10.712
Bye, Grandma.

20:11.440 --> 20:13.476
Every time that l hear <i>True Friend,</i>

20:13.520 --> 20:19.868
it always makes me think about...
About real friendship.

20:21.040 --> 20:24.953
Sorry. l had a little something
in my teeth. All better.

20:26.080 --> 20:27.911
As l was saying,
friendship means a lot to me.

20:27.960 --> 20:30.952
ln fact, this song was inspired by my...

20:35.480 --> 20:37.550
My best friend.

20:37.600 --> 20:39.192
She's been with me
through everything,

20:39.240 --> 20:41.959
and even though sometimes we fight,

20:43.000 --> 20:47.551
we know we'll always get through it
because, well, we love each other.

20:49.120 --> 20:51.395
And nothing says it better
than this song.

20:51.440 --> 20:53.192
''True friends will go to the ends
of the earth

20:53.240 --> 20:55.390
''till they find the things you need.

20:55.440 --> 20:57.351
''Friends hang on
through the ups and the downs...''

20:57.400 --> 20:58.913
Bless you.

20:59.880 --> 21:01.916
'''Cause they've got someone
to believe in.''

21:01.960 --> 21:04.838
Thank you for believing in me,
and thank you for this award.

21:04.880 --> 21:07.110
l love you all. Good night.

21:11.400 --> 21:13.550
-l'm sorry!
-Me, too!

21:21.800 --> 21:25.634
Let's go, ladies, pick your teams.

21:25.680 --> 21:28.797
You're slower than my husband
in the bathroom.

21:29.640 --> 21:31.949
-You said that last week.
-l know.

21:32.000 --> 21:36.949
Now he's got a mini-fridge in there.
l think he's hiding from me.

21:39.160 --> 21:42.197
-l could never imagine why.
-Yeah.

21:42.240 --> 21:45.277
Okay, l pick Joannie.

21:55.240 --> 21:57.708
Hey, you could've bet a quarter.

21:58.600 --> 21:59.669
l pick Lilly.

21:59.720 --> 22:01.915
lf you pick me,
you have to pick Miley, too.

22:01.960 --> 22:03.313
l don't want to pick her.

22:03.360 --> 22:08.070
-l don't care. Wherever l go, she goes.
-Yeah, we're kind of a package deal.

22:09.680 --> 22:12.399
Fine. l'll take Lilly and Stinky.

22:13.680 --> 22:16.433
Told you it would work. Now unlock us.

22:17.080 --> 22:19.275
l thought you had the key.

22:20.880 --> 22:23.075
-Man.
-Think fast!

